-- Heavy Rain in South China Affects 2.48 Million, Xinhua Reports
-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 2012-06-28T16:58:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-28/heavy-rain-in-south-china-affects-2-48-million-xinhua-reports.html
A total of 2.48 million people have
been affected by heavy rain in southern  China , Xinhua News
Agency reported, citing flood control authorities.  The rain has caused damage in seven provinces, including
Hunan, Guizhou, Jiangxi, Guangxi, Guangdong and Anhui, the
official news agency said.  To contact Bloomberg News staff for this story:
Feifei Shen in Beijing at 
 fshen11@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
